modules.description: Reads a file and extracts its metadata or content as a specific type, supporting source or target path contexts. Operates on data types conforming to the DATA_READABLE interface and path representations. Used to load structured data from files while preserving metadata for processing or validation.

Reads a file and extracts its metadata using a specified extraction strategy, or reads a file and returns only the parsed data. Operates on data types conforming to the DATA_READABLE interface and file paths. Used to process structured files where metadata extraction is required alongside data loading.

Provides functions to manage and execute build processes, including initializing a development environment and triggering builds. Operates with configuration settings and project metadata stored in local files. Used to set up isolated OCaml projects and compile them using Dune.

Loads structured data from files, extracting either full metadata, specific metadata via strategies, or just the parsed content, depending on configuration. Supports data types implementing the DATA_READABLE interface and handles source or target path contexts. Can load a YAML file and return its content as a typed value, extract specific fields from the metadata, or retrieve only the parsed document. Enables flexible processing of YAML files for validation, transformation, or integration with other systems.
